NCJKNCMFNHC: Five Mountains Hide the Little Village
JJANNCIOOBE: "Ten years ago today, we were shipwrecked on this island. We've been stranded here ever since."\n"Child, on this special day, Granny has a gift for you. It comes from Granny's hometown. Keep it safe, don't lose it. And don't forget the nursery rhyme Granny taught you."\n"...Five mountains hide the little village..."

NCJKNCMFNHC: Two Paths Through the Lonely Forest
JJANNCIOOBE: "I should give the family treasure to you, just to be safe."\n"Mommy's grandma said that it came from her hometown, far, far away. Mommy doesn't remember that place very well, because she got on a boat and left her hometown when she was very little. But maybe this nursery rhyme can help keep the memory of our hometown alive."\n"...Two paths through the lonely forest..."

NCJKNCMFNHC: One River Flowing Down the Middle
JJANNCIOOBE: "How time flies... In the blink of an eye, I've grown old... Ah! Hello darling, come to Grandma... Ooh! Goodness, someone's growing up fast aren't they? You're not a small child anymore!"\n"Now, what do you think this might be? Haha, it's a family heirloom. Grandma's ancestors brought it with them when they came here many years ago. Today, Grandma is giving it to you. Take it, and remember this nursery rhyme..."\n"...One river flowing down the middle..."

NCJKNCMFNHC: Four Winds Bring the Sound of Joy
JJANNCIOOBE: "Hey, guess what? Grandma gave me a gift, wanna see it? Here. Grandma says it comes from the world outside. She says our ancestors brought it to the island when they first came here."\n"Oh, and she taught me a nursery rhyme, too. Umm... I think it goes like this:"\n"...Four winds bring the sound of joy."

"The tides are getting higher by the year. If the water level rises much further, we will stand very little chance of survival..."
"There's no other choice. I must tell everyone to pack up their belongings and move to higher ground."
"Mother!"
"What's wrong?"
"The tide reached us, so I told everyone to run and get to higher ground. But the family heirloom — I'm sorry... It was a choice between that and getting everyone to safety, so I... I didn't have enough time to get it."
"It's right in the center of the island. If the water recedes sometime, or if someone gets in from outside, we'll just have to get them to find it for us."

"Hey, I found it! The other half of the ship, it's here! *sigh* After everything we went through with the army, all our hard-won treasure is gone, and so's the ship... When Chief Janome finds out, we'll be in for the scolding of a lifetime..."\n"This samurai puppet is all that's left. Hah... and we're no more capable of getting out of here on our own strength than it is."

"Oh no, the ship! This is Ako Domeki's pride and joy! I can't believe it... Ako only just gave us the ship, and now we're suddenly stranded here on this island in the middle of nowhere, and all our treasure's gone! We had this coming... This is our punishment! Oh, we never should have stolen that stupid puppet! Why, why did we—"\n"Shut it! We are going to fix Captain Ako's ship, you hear? No matter what it takes!"
"Hilichurls!? What are they doing here— Argh! G—Get off me... Help! Heeeelp!!!"
"No... Dongdong is still waiting for me to come home... *sigh* Oh, Dongdong, your father misses you... I hope you're finishing your meals and going to bed on time, like a good boy..."
"Hmm? Someone's here to rescue me...? Oh my... Thank you, you kind soul! Thank you, thank you!"
"But the General's a good guy, he protects us!"\n"I've told you, it's too dangerous... Hey! Where are you running off to?"
"The grown-ups say you come from a faraway land and that you're dressed like an army general... Don't you wanna talk to me? If not... it's okay if I give you this flower, right?"

"Mother says you're not one of us. But you protected us! Didn't you, General? ...Oh, I forgot... you won't talk to me."\n"Mother also says that your hometown is far away from here, just like ours. So far away that none of us even know where it is... General, do you ever miss your home?"

"Today we tried sailing in a fixed direction, but the boat kept returning to its starting point. Reason unclear..."
"Told you. We've been here long enough that we've already tried everything you could think of."
"Huh, as if you islanders would even know where to start. We are the pirates of Inazuma, feared all across the ocean! Maybe you could learn a thing or two from our expertise."
"The same expertise that got you stranded here?"
"...Bah!"

"Listen carefully! The fog in this area seems to come and go following a regular pattern! From morning to night, it gradually changes in distribution, thinning in some places while thickening in others. If my guess is correct... then the way out of these islands is hidden behind the fog. All we need to do is find it, then we can get everybody out of here!"\n"Really? Take me with you!"

"As long as we stay on this course, following the waves... We just need one good strong gust of wind."
"Well, as it happens, the wind direction changes in quite a unique way when the moon rises at this time of the year."
"Really? Are you sure?"
"Yep, I know the winds in these seas like the back of my hand!"

"What the... What happened to that rock?"
"If you look closely, you'll see it's just an illusion caused by the fog."
"Ah, wow... A mirage!"
"A 'mirage'...?"
"The fog is clearing — just like you said!"\n"Haha, we just need to keep sailing downwind and we'll be home free!"

Albedo: "This whole island is a chunk of Mondstadt mountain. A great force dislodged it from the mountain range and cast it into the sea. As it fell, it began to spin, and ultimately landed upside-down, hence the topography you see today."\nAlbedo: "Rather interesting. Another masterwork by the Anemo Archon, Barbatos, no doubt."

Kaeya: "Diluc, you're a man who knows his own mind. So, help me decide — is it seabird-hunting time or seashell-collecting time?"
Diluc: "...What is that supposed to mean?"
Kaeya: "Come now, Diluc, be nice! Do you really want to stay here and do nothing at all? We might as well find a way to pass the time. I simply thought collecting seashells might be fun. It was last time — although, we were much younger then."
Diluc: "I didn't know you still remembered anything from back then... Huh."

Klee: "Hehe, the fish from here must taste amazing! Klee really wants to try one..."
Barbara: "Alright, let's go catch some fish together! But we need to be quiet, okay? We mustn't let my big sister find out."
Klee: "Really? You like eating fish too?"
Barbara: "Haha, I sure do, but I like catching them even more! When we were kids, my sister and I used to go catching fish together sometimes. She might look super-serious now, but let me tell you, when she was a kid, she was so much fun. She even had a pet tortoise! Hehe, can you imagine?"
Razor: "Strange com... component..."\nRazor: "Razor hungry. Hungry for... fish."\nRazor: "Water on the left, and on the right... more water."

"We simply put the net here and wait. When the tide goes out, the fish will get caught in the net."\n"Wow, amazing!"\n"You like that, huh? Haha, the ancestors have a lot more wisdom where that came from."
"Hey! Do you hear that? That sound means the tide is coming in any second! We have to get to the top of the mountain! Here, climb up this vine, go!"
"What? You're saying you've been trapped on this island for... for generations!?"\n"Trapped or not, this is the only life we know. We can't leave..."\n"Good god... So are we... stuck here now, too?"

"No, just listen to me. There's a huge world out there! Mondstadt, Liyue, Inazuma... Compared to the size of those places, these islands are just a few pebbles in a pond!"\n"L—Liyue? What's that...?"\n"*sigh* Never mind, forget it. Alright. That's it then. The rest of my life, here... eating nuts and berries, and... waiting around to die."

"The ruins here are quite a sight to behold... But why are they upside-down?"\n"I don't know. They were here before our ancestors arrived... We took a lot of the stone to the different islands to use as building materials."
"We can't let the size of the ocean intimidate us. We have to at least try!"\n"You think we haven't tried before? We can't afford to lose anyone else!"
"I've seen it with my own eyes, people disappear into the fog and never return. So please... do not put yourself in danger!"

"Grandpa, everyone else has decided to leave. You're the only one left. Please, Grandpa, trust me... just this once. I promise you I've found the way out."\n"...*sigh* Very well. I will give you my trust. All of our fates now lie in your hands."

"Hey! Careful, you can't go napping here. You'll catch a cold. Go on, I'll take over. How is the sea — anything to report?"\n"Hmm...? Ugh, I must have fallen asleep... Oh! Uh, don't worry, no sign of the tide coming in so far."
"Quick! Sound the alarm! The tide is coming in!"
"Humanity's curiosity toward the stars is an instinct... If only I could decipher all the secrets to be told right here."
ANKBBLLLEBD: Obtained from the Mirage "The Ancient Azure Stars"

NCJKNCMFNHC: As the Poet Plies Parts of Ether and Earth
JJANNCIOOBE: "I have traveled far and wide in Inazuma since leaving home, and seen many new things along the way. Though material luxuries have not been a feature of my journey, it has yet been a rich and rewarding one, with the boundless earth and sky to call my abode, and all the wonders of nature as my partners in poetry."
ANKBBLLLEBD: Obtained from the Mirage "As the Courtyard in Spring Once Appeared: Part III"

NCJKNCMFNHC: As the Virtuoso Vouches for Verity and Valor
JJANNCIOOBE: "Music shows you what's in a person's soul. If you ain't got the courage, you can't play a strong tune. And if you don't keep it real, it won't reach anyone."

"Oz, my faithful escort through the darkness! Pave the way for thy Prinzessin with the truth thine eyes behold! All that is lowly escapes my gaze, it is but a mere illusion."\n"Is this to say that... a flaw unseen is a flaw that does not exist, mein Fräulein?"
ANKBBLLLEBD: Obtained from the Mirage "Immernachtreich Apokalypse: Part II"

JJANNCIOOBE:
"Yakov, what did the commander say to you that's got you so down?"
"Well, the waves were really choppy, so I slipped and fell while carrying the device. Fortunately, I was quick enough to save it..."
"But the commander still gave me an earful and ordered our squad to do signal reception tests. I mean, ugh, that's the toughest job around..."
"Oh come on, don't feel so down. We've done this stuff a hundred times before. Hey, chin up! Go get yourself something to eat!"

"Agafya, Persikov has ordered us to perform some signal reception tests. Looks like all four of us have to go... Chevka will probably get mad at me."\n"Come on, Yakov, orders are orders, Chevka isn't going to blame you for them!"\n"...You know what, if you're that scared, I'll go with you to talk to Chevka, alright?"

"Well, look who's back. Pfft. Well, at least you didn't wreck the device or anything."
"But..."
"Bah, it was just a signal reception test, not the end of the world."
"See? Chevka doesn't mind!"
"Well... Guess I'll make preparations. We'll head out later!"
NOHKKEJMHPM: The conches in various parts of the archipelago have been affected by the chaotic wavelengths present. This has caused them to film the scenery around. Touch them lightly to view an image of others projected from the mouth of the shell.

JJANNCIOOBE:
"Two signal testing sets..."
"You know, I honestly thought that he was in serious trouble this time. Who knew this was just about being assigned slightly more annoying work! So yeah, that was a relief."
"Hah! You should have seen how afraid he was of getting scolded by you. It was almost like watching a little brother cower at the thought of his older brother scolding him. Y'know... do you think he's just afraid of disappointing us? I mean, we're just squad-mates... but it does sometimes feel like we're family as well..."
"Family, huh..."

"Zakhar, are you alright? You've been clutching your stomach for a while now. Are you feeling a little queasy somewhere?"\n"No, no, Agafya. I'm fine. I probably just caught a chill last night. I'll be fine after a rest. Fine, I tell you!"

JJANNCIOOBE: "Agafya, let's take a break... Who knows whether we'll find anything to eat at all on these islands..."

JJANNCIOOBE: "Alright, Zakhar. We're done with the signal testing on this island... Let's hope the machine starts up without any issues..."\n"Okay, okay. But I couldn't care less about the kind of honor you keep talking about!"

"Don't worry about that, Zakhar. I'll take care of it... you just head up there and get a good rest."
